  "prompt": "How can I report someone on Quora?",
  "response": "Reporting someone on Quora is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### **Reporting a Profile**\n1. **Go to the user\u2019s profile**: Visit the profile of the person you want to report.\n2. **Click the three dots (\u2022\u2022\u2022)**: On their profile, click the three dots in the top-right corner.\n3. **Select \"Report\"**: From the dropdown menu, choose \"Report.\"\n4. **Choose a reason**: Select the reason for reporting (e.g., harassment, spam, misinformation).\n5. **Provide details**: Add any additional information or context to help Quora moderators understand the issue.\n6. **Submit**: Click \"Submit\" to send your report.\n\n### **Reporting a Post or Comment**\n1. **Locate the post or comment**: Find the specific post or comment you want to report.\n2. **Click the three dots (\u2022\u2022\u2022)**: Next to the post or comment, click the three dots.\n3. **Select \"Report\"**: Choose \"Report\" from the dropdown menu.\n4. **Choose a reason**: Select the appropriate reason for reporting.\n5. **Provide details**: Add any additional context if needed.\n6. **Submit**: Click \"Submit\" to send your report.\n\n### **After Reporting**\n- Quora\u2019s moderation team will review your report and take appropriate action, which may include warning the user, removing content, or suspending their account.\n- You may not receive a direct response from Quora about the outcome unless they need additional information from you.\n\nIf you feel the situation is urgent or involves serious violations (e.g., threats), consider reporting it to local authorities or using Quora\u2019s [Help Center](https://help.quora.com/) for further assistance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
